body:
@saguziel @artwr @aoen this is blocking rc2 for 1.8.1. I think this is the right fix and not #2236 as that only addresses it partially. 

Sub dags are run by the backfill logic and thus their dag runs get set to "backfill_XX" by convention. If you really find subdags with a dag run that has a run id of "scheduled_xx", please verify that this wasn't done manually and explain why it happens (cause I think it shouldn't). 

Can you please have a look?

Sorry for letting this PR languish with broken tests! I had assumed using `pytest` was acceptable, since it was employed in [an existing test](https://github.com/github/incubator-airflow/blob/1046513b706130587e7fb818e1911a7d9fcb7f8a/tests/contrib/hooks/zendesk_hook.py). However, it looks like that test has been modified to [no longer use `pytest`](https://github.com/github/incubator-airflow/blob/219c5064142c66cf8f051455199f2dda9b164584/tests/contrib/hooks/test_zendesk_hook.py). I'll make similar updates to this PR.

The previous version of this hook included a fair amount of error message reformatting. But there was no logic to actually recover from the errors; they were just re-raised with the original error hidden. I thought it might be better to remove that reformatting (in https://github.com/apache/incubator-airflow/pull/2206/commits/ead2f33b9c6051e65c147f8d34c7ec92c11d4544). However, I see that https://github.com/apache/incubator-airflow/commit/6dd4b3bc1f366e1f4f4b42d6781f1caee7a5827a added more error message reformatting (though the new method doesn't appear to be called anywhere).

@artwr @mistercrunch Would you prefer then I that I revert ead2f33b9c6051e65c147f8d34c7ec92c11d4544 and incorporate 6dd4b3bc1f366e1f4f4b42d6781f1caee7a5827a?

@vineet-rh @bolkedebruin 
Why was this PR closed or what would be needed to reopen the PR?
Unless there is a reason to not make airflow timezone aware,I can make a new PR if @vineet-rh is inactive or no longer interested.
